      "correctIndex": 2,
      "misconceptionFeedback": "⚠️ Common misconception! Power is the RATE of energy transfer, that is how fast energy is transferred, not how much. Since both transfer the same energy but Kettle A does it faster, Kettle A has the higher power.",
      "correctFeedback": "✓ Correct! Power = energy ÷ time. Kettle A transfers energy faster (same energy, less time), so it has a higher power. Power is about the RATE, not the total amount.",
